Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.73,0:00:04.44,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Reasoning and hints are interlinked,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.44,0:00:06.02,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Allowing us to understand a case's mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.56,0:00:08.02,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The Shinkansen is nearing Tokyo!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.44,0:00:09.53,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Can the two officers solve it in time?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.23,0:00:11.86,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Recognizing that single truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.86,0:00:13.74,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}a child with the intellect of an adult...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.74,0:00:15.49,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}His name is: Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.66,0:01:43.58,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}While traveling on the Shinkansen from Osaka,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.04,0:01:48.33,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}We ran into Officers Sato and Takagi,\Nwho were transporting a criminal.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.17,0:01:52.67,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Later, a bomb was found on the train...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.38,0:01:55.01,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Which Officer Sato went to investigate.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.55,0:02:01.14,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}At that time, while she was in the bathroom with it,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.14,0:02:03.81,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Officer Takagi had to take the criminal to the bathroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.77,0:02:07.85,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}And then, he apparently committed suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.85,0:02:08.39,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.94,0:02:20.61,Title,Sign,0,0,0,,The Bullet Train Transport Case\N(Part Two)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.54,0:02:26.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.91,0:02:28.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means this must be a murder case.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.04,0:02:31.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A-A murder case!?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.67,0:02:32.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.04,0:02:37.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,First, the criminal put the "bomb" in the\Nrear bathroom with the message on it...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.80,0:02:39.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To get me back there.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.22,0:02:46.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At an angle where Takagi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} couldn't see it,\Nhe gave the signal to go to the bathroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.98,0:02:53.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, he went to the toilet and faked his\Nsuicide with the fake blood and the knife.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.82,0:02:59.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next, they probably knew Takagi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} would\Nhandcuff him down and go get his partner.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.28,0:03:04.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then, the criminal, after seeing Takagi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} leave,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.16,0:03:09.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,came out from his hiding spot behind the sink curtain...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.46,0:03:13.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And killed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.21,0:03:20.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,B-But, the knife looked like it was deep inside him.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.30,0:03:25.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't see a knife in here when I first\Nopened the door for him either.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.72,0:03:30.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It must have been a fake knife, with a removable blade.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.69,0:03:35.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was probably hidden...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.11,0:03:39.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Back here, behind the baby changing board.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.86,0:03:42.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you put the blood, knife, and a memo here,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.07,0:03:46.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you could hide it back here where no one would look.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.74,0:03:47.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A memo?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.74,0:03:51.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The memo was just a lie to fool the victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.21,0:03:59.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It probably said, "I planted the bomb. Use\Nthe blood and the knife to fake a suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.71,0:04:03.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"After the officer leaves you, I'll cut off the\Nhandcuffs and free you during the explosion."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.59,0:04:09.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why didn't you just call Officer Sato with your cell phone?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.06,0:04:14.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, well, we were going through a long tunnel then...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.23,0:04:19.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that was directed in the memo.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.65,0:04:22.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The memo probably said:
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.74,0:04:27.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"When the train enters Shintanna Tunnel, do it."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.66,0:04:31.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But he was fooled.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.50,0:04:39.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But with this much blood loss, some of\Nit should've gotten on the criminal.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.88,0:04:40.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.17,0:04:45.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Someone would've noticed someone covered in blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.88,0:04:49.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was there anyone suspicious near your seat, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.68,0:04:56.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, I started watching the aisle\Nafter Officer Takagi came out...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.65,0:05:00.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Officer Takagi was the only one I noticed.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.23,0:05:09.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All things considered, the criminal must've come\Nfrom the back and went to the 13th row.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.41,0:05:12.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's gonna be tough finding this guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.16,0:05:14.83,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}What the...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.91,0:05:17.83,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Something else is on his hand aside from the fake blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.13,0:05:20.00,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.42,0:05:25.47,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I see, the murderer used that...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.35,0:05:31.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought I told you to watch him!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.89,0:05:39.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I just can't figure out how the criminal told him\Nto go to the bathroom with Takagi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} there...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.94,0:05:42.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Takagi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.15,0:05:43.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.86,0:05:48.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I went to the bathroom,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.16,0:05:51.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,did anyone do anything suspicious?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.87,0:05:54.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, not really...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.25,0:06:00.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Only two or three people passed by us after you left.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.63,0:06:03.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you remember their faces?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.00,0:06:05.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, I barely noticed them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.51,0:06:06.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I remember!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.05,0:06:10.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There were three that came by at that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.10,0:06:13.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There were two men with newspapers,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.39,0:06:15.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and one that had a newspaper and coffee.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.89,0:06:17.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, you could identify them?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.86,0:06:24.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the bathroom...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.73,0:06:26.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was a murder?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.65,0:06:30.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why do we have to talk to you police officers then?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.82,0:06:32.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, no...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.03,0:06:43.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We just think that one of you three may have sent the\Nvictim a signal telling him to go to the bathroom...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.88,0:06:45.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.92,0:06:49.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you mind telling us why you all went by our seats?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.30,0:06:54.18,Character Card,Sign,0,0,0,,Iwakuni Taturo\NPassenger (47)
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.14,0:06:54.51,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,I was four rows behind you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.39,0:06:59.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was so much commotion going on\Nthat I couldn't hear my horse racing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.64,0:07:02.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I had to move to the front.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.23,0:07:04.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.44,0:07:05.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And what about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.82,0:07:11.41,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Oh, I bought a can of coffee from the vending\Nmachine and was on my way back to my seat.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.11,0:07:09.78,Character Card,Sign,0,0,0,,Tokuyama Norio\NPassenger (51)
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.95,0:07:16.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then, I heard people saying there\Nwas a bomb in the bathroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.74,0:07:19.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I had no idea someone had been killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.08,0:07:21.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.46,0:07:26.34,Character Card,Sign,0,0,0,,Akashi Akira\NPassenger (29)
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.62,0:07:27.88,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,I heard about the bomb and decided to switch seats, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.34,0:07:34.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I believe Akashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Iwakuni{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} were\Nboth holding newspapers at the time?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.30,0:07:34.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.55,0:07:36.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I had one.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.51,0:07:41.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This guy was reading one at his seat, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.19,0:07:42.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I was...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.27,0:07:46.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well then, would you three go get your newspapers?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.69,0:07:54.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, and, Tokuyama{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, don't forget your coffee.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.66,0:08:06.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You three got on at the New Osaka Station\Nand bought your newspapers there?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.21,0:08:09.84,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Iwakuni{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} had "Horse Racing 7"...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.17,0:08:14.64,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Tokuyama{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} had "The Daily Morning Press" and a coffee...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.72,0:08:17.51,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Akashi{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} had "Nichiuri Sports"...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.39,0:08:23.35,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}None of them have "bathroom" written on them.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.44,0:08:27.02,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Besides, there has to be a hole...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.65,0:08:30.07,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The same goes for this coffee.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.61,0:08:36.11,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}How could you say "Go to the bathroom" with this?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.33,0:08:39.83,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Wait...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.99,0:08:42.33,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}This is actually...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.83,0:08:48.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What!? He stabbed himself in the bathroom?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.46,0:08:50.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Doesn't that mean it's a suicide?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.75,0:08:56.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, but it's fake because when\NI came back with my partner...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.09,0:08:59.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The knife had been pulled out and was in a weird position.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.30,0:09:05.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, isn't it likely he used two hands and\Nstood up since it wouldn't come out?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.77,0:09:08.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This guy is right!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.48,0:09:13.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can't know how it would fall if he stood up!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.99,0:09:18.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you all suspecting us over so little!?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.32,0:09:18.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, no...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.91,0:09:23.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Besides, once we get to Tokyo, you can't keep me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.70,0:09:24.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Same here!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.33,0:09:26.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Me, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.92,0:09:29.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Uncle?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.75,0:09:31.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.92,0:09:36.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you remember what you bought at New Osaka Station?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.80,0:09:37.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.93,0:09:38.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.64,0:09:43.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Horse Racing 7", "Nichiuri Sports", and a can of coffee.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.31,0:09:46.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, and two packs of cigarettes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.94,0:09:49.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.23,0:09:52.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.40,0:09:56.82,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}As I thought...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.99,0:10:03.41,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The criminal is the one who made that comment.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.87,0:10:05.58,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I know...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.37,0:10:09.33,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}How you got him to come to the bathroom...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.96,0:10:11.54,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}How you killed him...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.84,0:10:13.96,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I know everything...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.51,0:10:19.05,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Including the weak point you overlooked.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.56,0:10:33.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Suicide, suicide! The guy killed himself!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.82,0:10:38.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since this isn't a murder, we aren't needed.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.66,0:10:40.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.99,0:10:43.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well then, that's that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.74,0:10:46.54,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10\an8}Thank you for riding.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.54,0:10:49.12,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10\an8}We are now arriving at Tokyo.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.12,0:10:50.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Seeya.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.12,0:10:52.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I have things I must attend to.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.83,0:10:53.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-Wait...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.46,0:10:58.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're already in enough trouble\Nfor letting the victim get killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.13,0:11:02.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If his murderer gets away...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.05,0:11:03.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It'll get much worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.22,0:11:07.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Especially Takagi, who was with him at the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.14,0:11:08.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He won't get off easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.31,0:11:10.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,N-No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.06,0:11:12.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But don't worry!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.56,0:11:15.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's always a job down at my agency.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.36,0:11:17.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I need an assistant.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.62,0:11:30.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.54,0:11:34.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As much as I'd like to, Takagi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.54,0:11:38.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't bring you on as an assistant.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.67,0:11:47.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll have to see your best work as an\Nofficer before I can consider that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.77,0:11:54.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like, let's start with you getting\Nthe murderer right behind you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.52,0:11:56.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.07,0:11:59.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You mean, you've...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.23,0:12:00.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Figured out who the criminal is?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.49,0:12:08.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'll begin at how the criminal conveyed the message,\N"Go to the bathroom" without Takagi noticing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.33,0:12:16.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here are the items the three suspects had...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.59,0:12:19.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Newspapers and the coffee.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.38,0:12:21.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't you see it, Takagi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.42,0:12:24.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right there is a message telling him to go to the bathroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.26,0:12:26.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-Where?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.39,0:12:28.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where does it say that?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.60,0:12:32.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You don't see it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.35,0:12:36.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Bathroom... initials...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.81,0:12:42.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The initials of "Water Closet", "W.C.", are used everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.20,0:12:45.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Something else also uses those initials...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.00,0:12:54.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takagi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.54,0:12:56.21,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Could it be...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.71,0:13:01.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The World Cup!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.51,0:13:02.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.80,0:13:06.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When the criminal went by carrying his newspaper,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.26,0:13:14.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,he pointed to "World Cup" on his paper in\Norder to silently say: "Go to the bathroom."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.39,0:13:16.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.73,0:13:19.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The one who had the sports newspaper...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.11,0:13:21.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Akashi Akira{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.07,0:13:28.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't joke around!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.53,0:13:32.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Having a sports newspaper doesn't make me a criminal!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.58,0:13:33.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's true...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.62,0:13:41.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's hard to immediately think of "W.C."\Nby just seeing "World Cup", isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.34,0:13:45.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's another reason Akashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} put\Nthe bomb in that back bathroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.47,0:13:53.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With that bathroom incident just happening, the\Nword "bathroom" was already in his head.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.77,0:14:05.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, by pointing to "World Cup" on the paper, you could\Ntake advantage of the timing and make him go there.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.74,0:14:17.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's likely that he bought tickets at the same time Takagi did, and then waited around until the three of you got on board.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.71,0:14:19.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This way, he had time to plan the murder...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.05,0:14:24.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,S-Stop that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.06,0:14:26.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What're you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.39,0:14:28.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.35,0:14:30.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought you were really asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.52,0:14:32.56,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Hey, hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.98,0:14:38.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've heard about it before, but this is my\Nfirst time seeing "Sleeping Kogoro".
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.61,0:14:39.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Sleeping Kogoro"?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.57,0:14:42.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That famous detective?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.41,0:14:46.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't care you're "Sleeping"...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.87,0:14:52.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you sure? You have no proof that this was a murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.79,0:14:54.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is a murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.79,0:14:58.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The direction of the knife is too unusual otherwise.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.01,0:15:06.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As I said earlier, he must've stood up and used\Nboth hands because it wouldn't come out.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.60,0:15:10.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why would you have to stand up to take\Nthe knife out with both hands?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.94,0:15:13.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you an idiot?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.36,0:15:15.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He couldn't use his left hand unless he stood up.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.98,0:15:26.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, his left hand was handcuffed to the safety bar\Nat the time, so he couldn't do it without standing up.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.29,0:15:29.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But isn't that strange...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.62,0:15:33.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How would you know that without visiting the crime scene?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.46,0:15:36.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just an assumption!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.04,0:15:40.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You said the guy stabbed himself and\Nthen the officer left to get his partner.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.13,0:15:44.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I assumed that he handcuffed him to the safety bar.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.05,0:15:48.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, but how'd you know he was wearing handcuffs?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.85,0:15:51.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I passed by this officer,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.35,0:15:54.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That guy had a cloth over his hands!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.98,0:15:59.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, how'd you know the murdered man was him?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.69,0:16:02.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's the word going around...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.24,0:16:07.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway, if you plan on making me\Nyour lead suspect, get some proof!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.16,0:16:10.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Were my fingerprints on the knife?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.75,0:16:13.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is there any blood on me?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.08,0:16:16.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course there's no blood on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.92,0:16:20.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You had him hold the newspaper...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.09,0:16:24.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And stabbed him through it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.76,0:16:30.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The proof is what has been left on his right hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.18,0:16:35.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The newspaper left an imprint on his hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.81,0:16:40.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see, that means the blood would splatter on the newspaper.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.98,0:16:42.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What're you saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.69,0:16:44.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look at my newspaper!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.15,0:16:46.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no blood or holes in it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.91,0:16:48.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why you bought two, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.03,0:16:49.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What!?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.74,0:16:54.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why you bought two copies of "Nichiuri Sports".
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.91,0:16:55.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, Conan?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.29,0:16:59.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See? It's the same as your newspaper!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.79,0:17:02.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Those guys seen me before, I didn't have two newspapers!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.84,0:17:04.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah-le-le...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.84,0:17:06.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's something weird about this paper.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.22,0:17:12.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look at this newspaper that Uncle Kogoro bought...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.14,0:17:15.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then look at your newspaper.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.94,0:17:18.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They look the same, but the words are different.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.32,0:17:22.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.86,0:17:26.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dad's paper says: "World Cup Hero Arrested",
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.70,0:17:30.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,while the other says: "World Cup Hero Questioned".
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.08,0:17:35.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The ones at the station and the stores are different.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.46,0:17:40.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Unlike the newspapers at stores, the ones\Nsold at stations have a later deadline.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.92,0:17:42.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That gives them time to change them if need be.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.59,0:17:47.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since his arrest was such big news, they had to change it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.34,0:17:51.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, Akashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} bought this newspaper at...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.68,0:17:53.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is what probably happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.35,0:17:56.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He got this one to lure the victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.94,0:18:06.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then, he bought another one at the station while he\Nwas waiting to prevent the blood from getting on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.57,0:18:15.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He bought two was just in case someone noticed he\Ndidn't have a paper after the crime was committed.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.95,0:18:17.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's not it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.16,0:18:21.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I bought another because of the headline!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.63,0:18:24.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, could you show me?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.84,0:18:27.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The other Nichiuri Sports paper.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.84,0:18:28.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.68,0:18:34.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You probably ripped it up and\Nflushed it down the toilet, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.27,0:18:37.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we check the toilet's tank, we'll find it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.11,0:18:47.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.78,0:18:54.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Enough!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.30,0:19:11.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, admit it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.84,0:19:14.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Amazing, Officer Takagi!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.80,0:19:16.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess we're straight...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.97,0:19:18.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, nothing...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.64,0:19:23.69,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Soon after Inspector Megure and the\Nothers arrived at the station in Tokyo,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.27,0:19:25.77,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The criminal was arrested...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.52,0:19:28.15,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}And taken to the station.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.20,0:19:34.28,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The reason he did it was to make\Nsure the drug route stayed secret.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.37,0:19:41.96,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But, unfortunately for him, the Police found\None of the dealers and shut down their route.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.25,0:19:47.34,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Somehow, it saved Officers Sato and Takagi's jobs...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.13,0:19:51.05,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}And Officer Takagi was saved from\Nbecoming Uncle's assistant.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.73,0:21:24.73,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}And then:
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.73,0:21:26.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A pay cut, a pay cut!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.81,0:21:28.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A pay cut for three months!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.02,0:21:30.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's not fair.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.52,0:21:34.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You know, this pay cut will be on your record forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.40,0:21:36.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I know...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.86,0:21:37.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, don't worry!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.53,0:21:41.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you ever get fired, you can always get married.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.28,0:21:43.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't need marriage...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.54,0:21:47.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm here to preserve and protect the city.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.83,0:21:50.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the problem is Takagi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.63,0:21:55.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If he doesn't get going, he'll be a\Nlowly first-grade investigator forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.22,0:21:58.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, by the way, Yumi...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.35,0:22:02.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you like Takagi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.44,0:22:16.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's with that reaction?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.03,0:22:21.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since I'm older than you, I need to know this kind of stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.03,0:22:23.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess so...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.95,0:22:26.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So? Do you...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.25,0:22:27.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like him?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.37,0:22:29.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me you're in love!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.67,0:22:31.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not at all...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.00,0:22:34.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's what I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.42,0:22:38.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was bumbling around about how he got a ticket from you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.18,0:22:41.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, stop fooling around with Takagi.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.97,0:22:44.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You should hurry and find a real man.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.93,0:22:46.81,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}She fell for it...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.31,0:22:49.23,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Miwako fell for it...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.85,0:22:52.73,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}She fell for my love ticket plan!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.52,0:22:58.11,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}All right! I should call the other one who got their wage cut.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.11,0:22:59.28,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}This'll cheer him up!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.41,0:23:02.41,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}You should hurry and find a real man.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.12,0:23:03.78,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.58,0:23:08.79,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Why am I helping them out so much?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.79,0:23:09.37,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It's so stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.00,0:23:16.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thanks for coming by to give your statements.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.96,0:23:17.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.13,0:23:20.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, don't be so down.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.05,0:23:22.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You'll bounce back sometime.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.26,0:23:28.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Takagi, straighten up!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.30,0:23:30.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,S-S-Straight—!?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.63,0:23:33.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We've got that case on 4th! Let's hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.18,0:23:34.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, ma'am!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.05,0:23:37.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Officer Sato seems cheerful.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.47,0:23:40.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't she get the same pay cut as Takagi?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.56,0:23:42.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe something good happened.
